frus:attachment.p:
His last report Easter, 1842, says: He lacked steadiness; Latin, read
                                Caesar and Ovid very well; Greek, satisfactory; German, good;
                                French, good; mathematics, satisfactory. A note says: Very prompt in
                                the independent working of problems; natural history, middling;
                                history and geography, good. He was fourteen years old when he left
                                school, and will therefore this year reach his fiftieth year.
